Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale-red pottery vessel, the fabric is relatively coarse and greyish in section, the interior is very worn, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (394032) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/394032)
